result.execSummary:
The defendant Kelly L. Brown was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 1:38 p.m. Defendant Kelly L. Brown in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant has complied with all of the terms of the Deferred Sentencing Agreement. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. DE waives right to counsel. Court accepts voluntary waiver of counsel. No statement by DE. Court orders: Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court. Bond previously posted to be applied. Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal rights given.

3:10 pm case called. Defendant Kelly L. Brown in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on the record by DA Blader-deferred sentencing for 6 months.   Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: No Contest. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright the use of dangerous weapon enhancer.   Court deferrs sentencing for 6 months.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 17, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Pre-trial conference at 11-12-2015 09:15 am.
Status conference at 12-04-2015 01:40 pm.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons, capable of causing injury to another.

Case Called @ 1:42 PM: Defendant Kelly L. Brown in court, appearing pro se.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish counsel today.  NGP received and entered.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 12, 2015 at 09:15 am.  Status conference scheduled for December 4, 2015 at 01:40 pm.
